                type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On July 31, the Department of State announced in circular 45 the establishment of
                    the United States Information Agency (<gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss>).
                    The text of this circular is printed in Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, August 24, 1953, pages 239–240. The previous day, President
                        <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWERGADD1">Eisenhower</persName> had named
                        <persName corresp="#p_STREIBERTTC1">Theodore C. Streibert</persName> of
                    Locust Valley, New York, as the <gloss target="#t_USIA1">USIA</gloss>’s first
                    director. The text of the White House announcement of <persName
                        corresp="#p_STREIBERTTC1">Streibert</persName>’s designation is printed <hi
                        rend="italic">ibid</hi>., page 238.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
